# Stimulus UI (Fantager)

Full spec: `docs/ui-guidelines.md` §9.

## Translations

- **Never** hardcode user-facing strings in JS
- Pass copy via `data-*-value` from Twig (`js_flash.*` keys in `translations/messages.*.yaml`)
- Format numbers/dates with `assets/utils/locale.js` — not `'cs-CZ'` literals

## DOM & styling

- Toggle **existing** classes from Twig (e.g. `hidden`, `alert-success`) — do not inject Tailwind utilities
- Dynamic markup: clone `<template id="template-…">` nodes from Twig (marketplace, notifications, ledger)
- Do not build HTML strings with `class="flex gap-2 …"` in controllers

## Alerts

Use `assets/utils/alert.js`. Target elements must already have `.alert` base class in Twig; JS toggles type modifier + `hidden`.

## Structure

```javascript
static targets = ['…'];
static values = { confirmMessage: String };

connect() { /* bind */ }
disconnect() { /* cleanup timers/listeners if added globally */ }
```

## a11y

- After opening modals, manage focus
- Icon buttons in injected content must keep `aria-label` from template

## Optional verification (user-requested only)

Do not run automatically. When the user asks:

```bash
bash scripts/check-ui-compliance.sh
```
